Readying himself to dodge out of the way in case something came flying towards him, Cody cautiously pressed on the
mechanism at the front of the box. The container failed to open. Pulling out his credit card, Cody slid it between box
and lid, and, feeling it catch, gently pressed the plastic against the back of the latch. The lock sprang open; Cody,
after holding his breath a moment, relaxed and smiled.
